    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The downside of my tooltip over the patch was that finding all the neighbors was very CPU expensive (at least the way I implemented it) although usability was nice. An easier to implement approach suggested by @pchote was to allow a selection square lasso similar to how the mine layer works, but probably with just the borders rendered not sprite overlays (like we did the minelayer in past releases) and then update the counter at the top accordingly.\n"
